PROBLEM STATEMENT¶

We are solving is the prediction of the future labours earning.¶

SOLUTION APPROACH¶

As we need to predict Labour earning for 1978 which is continuous in nature, Linear Regression can be used for prediction¶

SPLITING OF DEPENDENT VARIABLE & INDEPENDENT VARIABLE¶

SPLITING OF TRAIN & TEST DATA

In [25]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test=train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.2,random_state=1)

STEP 4: MODEL BUILDING¶

In [26]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
lr=LinearRegression()

FITTING THE TRAIN DATA¶

In [27]:

Out[27]:

DATA OVERFITTING VALIDATION¶

In [28]:

PREDICTION¶
